doc.ContractDescription: THIS WORK WILL APPLY RETRIEVAL ALGORITHMS THAT ARE CURRENTLY IN USE FOR GEOTASO TRACE GAS RETRIEVALS AND OMI GOME 2 OZONE PROFILE RETRIEVALS AT SMITHSONIAN ASTROPHYSICAL OBSERVATORY, AND ARE THE HERITAGE ALGORITHMS FOR FUTURE TEMPO RETRIEVALS. 1. WE WILL APPLY RETRIEVAL ALGORITHMS TO DETERMINE TRACE GAS COLUMN AMOUNTS OF O3, HCHO AND SO2 FROM GEOTASO SPECTRA, WILL ASSESS AND FINE TUNE INSTRUMENT WAVELENGTH AND RADIOMETRIC CALIBRATION WITH FLIGHT DATA, AND WILL PERFORM COMPARISONS WITH GROUND, AIRCRAFT AND SATELLITE MEASUREMENTS COLLECTED BY OTHER INSTRUMENTS DURING THE CAMPAIGN. WE WILL APPLY THE RADIATIVE TRANSFER MODEL VLIDORT TO DETERMINE VERTICALLY RESOLVED SCATTERING WEIGHTS FOR CONVERSION OF RETRIEVED SLANT COLUMN DENSITIES TO VERTICAL COLUMN DENSITIES. 2. WE WILL ALSO PERFORM TROPOSPHERIC OZONE PROFILE RETRIEVAL FROM GEOTASO UV, AND UV VISIBLE MEASUREMENTS USING THE OPTIMAL ESTIMATION TECHNIQUE. AS ABSOLUTE RADIOMETRIC CALIBRATION IS IMPORTANT TO THE OZONE PROFILE RETRIEVALS, WE WILL PERFORM RADIATIVE TRANSFER SIMULATIONS TO ASSESS THE RADIOMETRIC CALIBRATION AND DERIVE EMPIRICAL CORRECTION TO RADIANCE SPECTRA. THE RETRIEVALS WILL BE VALIDATED AGAINST OTHER CORRELATIVE MEASUREMENTS DURING THE CAMPAIGN. THE UV RETRIEVALS WILL ALSO BE COMPARED WITH THE UV VISIBLE RETRIEVALS.
